    <scopecontent id="aspace_bf603f8f12224c24c37450711560921b">
      <head>Scope and Contents</head>
      <p>The papers consist of material pertaining to Louise M. Switzer and her family.  Items include a wedding book and invitation, genealogical material, photographs (which also include the Romaine family), and a parasol with the monogram "L.M.S." The Switzer family resided on Putnam Avenue in Brooklyn in the late 19th and early 20th centuries.</p>
      <p>The books in the collection include: <emph render="italic">The Revellers</emph>, by Rev. Edward A. Monroe (1849), <emph render="italic">Tales of a Wayside Inn</emph>, by Henry Wadsworth Longfellow (1928), and one Holy Bible (circa 1875).</p>
    </scopecontent>
